main event: Two objects were detected and tracked by ground-radar in Bremerton, Washington in July 1962.
interesting points: The weather was overcast and rainy, preventing visual confirmation of the objects., The report suggests that the objects might have been high-performance aircraft based on civilian observations., No information was available regarding the size, speed, or altitude of the objects., The sighting was reported to the 8th AIS Sq by radar site personnel., A shooting star or astronomical phenomenon was considered as a potential explanation for the radar detection.
sighted object: two unidentified objects on ground-radar screen
witness description: Radar site personnel without visual confirmation due to weather conditions.
